---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout title="Is TA a Scrabble Word? Yes — 2 Points (TWL + SOWPODS)" description="TA is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points. British informal for thank you. Learn extensions like TAX (10pts) and board placement strategy." keywords="is ta a scrabble word, ta scrabble, ta valid, two letter words scrabble, ta word score">
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Is TA a Scrabble Word? Yes — 2 Points (TWL + SOWPODS)","description":"TA is a valid Scrabble word worth 2 points in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries. British informal for thank you.","datePublished":"2026-06-29","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/is-ta-a-scrabble-word"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is TA a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. TA is valid in both TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 2 points (T=1, A=1)."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does TA mean in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"TA is British informal for 'thank you'. It is accepted as a valid two-letter word in all official Scrabble dictionaries."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What words can you make from TA in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"TA extends to TAB (5pts), TAD (4pts), TAG (4pts), TAN (3pts), TAP (5pts), TAR (3pts), TAT (3pts), and TAX (10pts)."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Two-Letter Words</span>
      </nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Is TA a Scrabble Word? Yes — 2 Points</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>3 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Looking up whether <strong class="text-white">TA</strong> is playable in Scrabble? It absolutely is. TA is valid in both the TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, worth 2 points, and opens one of the best high-value extensions in the game.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-green-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-950/30 to-emerald-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-green-500/70">✓ VALID</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">TA</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-green-300 font-semibold mb-3">2 Points · T(1) + A(1) · British informal for "thank you"</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Valid in TWL (Tournament Word List) and SOWPODS. A common two-letter word used to open parallel plays and set up high-value extensions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">2</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Points</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">Both</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Dictionaries</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">T-tiles in bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A-tiles available</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Extensions from TA</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">TA might score only 2 points on its own, but the extensions are where the real value lives. Adding one letter can multiply your score dramatically.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAB</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAD</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAG</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">4pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAN</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAP</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">5pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAR</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAT</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">3pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">TAX</span><span class="text-blue-400 text-xs">10pts</span></span>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy: Why TA Matters</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">TA is a setup word. Its real power is unlocking TAX — a 10-point three-letter word that lands your X tile efficiently. Place the T on a Double Word Score and you double the entire word for 20 points from just three tiles.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> TA is low-scoring alone but opens TAX (10pts). Always think one move ahead when placing TA — leave room to extend.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> T on a DWS doubles the entire word. TA on DWS = 4pts. TAX on DWS = 20pts. The positional value far outweighs the base score.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Tip:</span> Compare TA with TI — both score 2pts, but TA has 8 extensions while TI has fewer high-value plays. Prefer TA when planning ahead.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">TA vs TI — Same Score, Different Paths</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Both TA and TI score 2 points, but their extension trees differ significantly. TA leads to TAX (10pts) while TI leads to TIC (5pts) and TIP (5pts). If you're holding an X, TA is the superior play every time.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">TA's value isn't in the 2 points it scores — it's in the <span class="text-white font-medium">TAX extension (10pts)</span> it enables. Think of TA as a deposit on a future high-scoring play.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/is-ti-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is TI a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/is-er-a-scrabble-word/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Is ER a Scrabble Word?</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-cyan-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-200 dark:border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-800 dark:text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Check any word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up required</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
